{"source_url": "https://museums.iastate.edu/event/explore-artful-engineering-and-technology", "title": "Explore! Artful Engineering and Technology", "description": "Explore the fascinating connections between art and technology at the Brunnier Art Museum. Free activities and crafts for children and families will focus on cityscapes, mapmaking, 3D modeling, and technology. | Tags: Family Programs", "venue_name": "University Museums - Iowa State University", "location_text": "Brunnier Art Museum", "city": "Ames", "state": "IA", "activity_type": "workshop", "age_min": null, "age_max": null, "drop_in": false, "registration_required": false, "start_at": "2026-02-28T10:00:00", "end_at": "2026-02-28T13:00:00", "timezone": "America/Chicago", "free_verification_status": "confirmed", "is_free": true}
{"source_url": "https://museums.iastate.edu/event/gallery-talk-albert-paley-origins-anne-pagel", "title": "Gallery Talk: \u201cAlbert Paley: Origins\u201d with Anne Pagel", "description": "Discover the work of internationally recognized metal sculptor Albert Paley in this free guest lecture. Anne Pagel, Curator of the Karen and Robert Duncan Art Collection, explores how Paley transforms metal into bold, evolving sculptures that investigate form, materials, and innovation. Learn how his sculptures create a dynamic dialogue between art and architecture in public spaces, including Iowa State\u2019s own Transformation, a public art installation at the east entrance of Morrill Hall. | Tags: Lectures & Talks", "venue_name": "University Museums - Iowa State University", "location_text": "Christian Petersen Art Museum", "city": "Ames", "state": "IA", "activity_type": "talk", "age_min": null, "age_max": null, "drop_in": false, "registration_required": false, "start_at": "2026-03-01T14:00:00", "end_at": "2026-03-01T15:00:00", "timezone": "America/Chicago", "free_verification_status": "confirmed", "is_free": true}
{"source_url": "https://museums.iastate.edu/event/tech-meets-tradition-preserving-campus-art-materials-engineering", "title": "Tech Meets Tradition: Preserving Campus Art with Materials Engineering", "description": "In conjunction with the exhibition \"Terra Cotta Conservation in the Art on Campus Collection,\" materials engineer Sawyer Krotz will join curator Sydney Marshall for a dynamic exploration of how technology is shaping the future of the conservation of sculpture. Following a guided tour of the exhibition, watch a live demonstration of object scanning and learn how these tools can support the preservation and restoration of public art. | Tags: Workshops, Lectures & Talks, Tours", "venue_name": "University Museums - Iowa State University", "location_text": "Christian Petersen Art Museum", "city": "Ames", "state": "IA", "activity_type": "talk", "age_min": null, "age_max": null, "drop_in": false, "registration_required": false, "start_at": "2026-03-10T17:30:00", "end_at": "2026-03-10T18:30:00", "timezone": "America/Chicago", "free_verification_status": "uncertain", "is_free": null}
{"source_url": "https://museums.iastate.edu/event/explore-america-250-memory-and-belonging", "title": "Explore! America 250 \u2013 Memory and Belonging", "description": "Make memories at the museum! As we celebrate America 250 at the Farm House Museum, we reflect on how memory shapes our knowledge of history and our sense of belonging. How do you create memories that last? What will you create to mark this moment in time? Let\u2019s Explore! Enjoy multiple free, commemorative crafts and activities along with treats. | Tags: Family Programs", "venue_name": "University Museums - Iowa State University", "location_text": "Farm House Museum", "city": "Ames", "state": "IA", "activity_type": "workshop", "age_min": null, "age_max": null, "drop_in": false, "registration_required": false, "start_at": "2026-03-28T10:00:00", "end_at": "2026-03-28T13:00:00", "timezone": "America/Chicago", "free_verification_status": "uncertain", "is_free": null}
{"source_url": "https://museums.iastate.edu/event/myths-self-stephanie-brunia", "title": "Myths of the Self with Stephanie Brunia", "description": "Explore how artist Stephanie Brunia (American, born 1984) employs photography to examine the intangible and create stories drawn from deep personal narratives. In conjunction with the exhibition Tell Me a Story, visit Brunia\u2019s photographs on view and learn more about her history and process of visual storytelling. | Tags: Lectures & Talks", "venue_name": "University Museums - Iowa State University", "location_text": "Brunnier Art Museum", "city": "Ames", "state": "IA", "activity_type": "talk", "age_min": null, "age_max": null, "drop_in": false, "registration_required": false, "start_at": "2026-04-12T14:00:00", "end_at": "2026-04-12T15:00:00", "timezone": "America/Chicago", "free_verification_status": "uncertain", "is_free": null}
{"source_url": "https://museums.iastate.edu/event/iowa-eats-reflections-class-cookbooks", "title": "Iowa Eats: Reflections from Class Cookbooks", "description": "Every recipe has a story! Recipes often reveal cultural identity, childhood memories, and traditions passed through kitchens. | Tags: Lectures & Talks", "venue_name": "University Museums - Iowa State University", "location_text": "Virtual", "city": "Ames", "state": "IA", "activity_type": "talk", "age_min": null, "age_max": null, "drop_in": false, "registration_required": false, "start_at": "2026-04-16T17:30:00", "end_at": "2026-04-16T18:30:00", "timezone": "America/Chicago", "free_verification_status": "uncertain", "is_free": null}
{"source_url": "https://museums.iastate.edu/event/explore-today-was-fairytale", "title": "Explore! Today Was a Fairytale", "description": "Explore new stories and create your own at the Brunnier Art Museum! Activities and crafts for children and families will focus on imagination and storytelling. Enjoy the exhibition Tell Me a Story and the many works of art on view. Participants are encouraged to come dressed as their favorite fairytale character. Activities geared for grades K-5; all are welcome. Stop by any time during the three-hour window, while supplies last. No admission fee or registration. Free, easy parking. | Tags: Family Programs", "venue_name": "University Museums - Iowa State University", "location_text": "Brunnier Art Museum", "city": "Ames", "state": "IA", "activity_type": "workshop", "age_min": null, "age_max": null, "drop_in": false, "registration_required": false, "start_at": "2026-04-25T10:00:00", "end_at": "2026-04-25T13:00:00", "timezone": "America/Chicago", "free_verification_status": "uncertain", "is_free": null}
{"source_url": "https://museums.iastate.edu/event/tell-me-story-roundtable-conversation", "title": "Tell Me a Story Roundtable Conversation", "description": "Join ISU faculty and University Museums in a conversational roundtable to learn about the impact of storytelling on teaching and research. Participants will also discuss personal connections to the works of art in the exhibition, Tell Me a Story. | Tags: Lectures & Talks", "venue_name": "University Museums - Iowa State University", "location_text": "Brunnier Art Museum", "city": "Ames", "state": "IA", "activity_type": "talk", "age_min": null, "age_max": null, "drop_in": false, "registration_required": false, "start_at": "2026-04-30T17:00:00", "end_at": "2026-04-30T18:00:00", "timezone": "America/Chicago", "free_verification_status": "uncertain", "is_free": null}
{"source_url": "https://museums.iastate.edu/event/university-museums-parks", "title": "University Museums @ Parks!", "description": "Need a study break? Get creative with University Museums! Swing by the second-floor rotunda at Parks Library for drawing activities inspired by ISU\u2019s Art on Campus Collection. Spark your creativity and unwind before diving back into studying! Provided in partnership with Iowa State University Library and ISU Student Wellness. | Tags: Workshops", "venue_name": "University Museums - Iowa State University", "location_text": "Parks Library", "city": "Ames", "state": "IA", "activity_type": "workshop", "age_min": null, "age_max": null, "drop_in": false, "registration_required": false, "start_at": "2026-05-05T12:00:00", "end_at": null, "timezone": "America/Chicago", "free_verification_status": "uncertain", "is_free": null}
